     In unusual case, Waterford, Va., declined offer from Benchmark

     In unusual case, Waterford, Va., declined offer from Benchmark
Communications (22,300 subscribers in Loudoun County) to wire
small, historic town of 250 homes.  Residents argued that lines on
utility poles would ruin historic flavor.  Company then agreed to
poll residents.  After reportedly receiving only about 40
responses, about half of which were against idea, company dropped
plans.  Case is believed to be one of few instances ever of
community declining cable.



