INVENTION FOR NONCONTACT REMOVAL OF ORGANIC COATINGS
FROM THE SURFACE OF PAINTINGS [960111]

This Government-owned patent application (NASA),
available for licensing, discloses a method for
removing organic soils and protective coatings from a
painting.  Degraded protective coatings, such as
lacquers, acrylics, natural resins, carbons, soot, and
polyurethane, are safely removed from the surface of a
painting without contact to the surface of the
painting.  The method can be used for restoration of
paintings when they have been damaged through age,
fire, etc.

